Create test ONNX proto object.

Creates an identity graph
with input and output nodes
of the given `shapes`.
For each entry an input and output
node will be created.
`-1`, `None` or strings
define a dynamic axis.
Per node,
one dynamic axis is allowed.
The identity graph can be used as `path` argument
of {class}`audonnx.Model`.

Args:

: shapes: list with shapes defining the identical

  : input and output nodes of the model graph

  dtype: data type, see [supported data types]
  opset_version: opset version

Returns:

: ONNX object

Examples:
: ```pycon
  >>> create_model_proto([[2]])
  ir_version: 9
  opset_import {
    version: 14
  }
  producer_name: "test"
  graph {
    node {
      input: "input-0"
      output: "output-0"
      op_type: "Identity"
    }
    name: "test"
    input {
      name: "input-0"
      type {
        tensor_type {
          elem_type: 1
          shape {
            dim {
              dim_value: 2
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
    output {
      name: "output-0"
      type {
        tensor_type {
          elem_type: 1
          shape {
            dim {
              dim_value: 2
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
  <BLANKLINE>
  ```

[supported data types]: https://onnxruntime.ai/docs/reference/operators/custom-python-operator.html#supported-data-types
